## 1. EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

YDY HRM Enterprise is a comprehensive Human Resource Management System designed to streamline and automate all aspects of human capital management. Built with modern PHP technology stack and featuring a responsive web interface, this system provides organizations with complete control over their workforce management processes.

### Key Features:
- Complete employee lifecycle management
- Advanced attendance and leave management
- Performance evaluation and talent acquisition
- Robust reporting and analytics
- Multi-level security and audit trails
- Mobile-responsive design
- Real-time dashboard and notifications

---

## 2. SYSTEM OVERVIEW

### 2.1 System Purpose
YDY HRM Enterprise serves as a centralized platform for managing all human resource operations within an organization. The system eliminates manual processes, reduces administrative overhead, and provides data-driven insights for strategic decision-making.

### 2.2 Target Users
- HR Administrators and Managers
- Department Heads and Team Leaders
- Employees (self-service features)
- System Administrators
- Executive Management

### 2.3 Core Objectives
- Automate routine HR tasks
- Improve data accuracy and consistency
- Enhance compliance and audit capabilities
- Provide actionable business intelligence
- Streamline employee experience

---

## 3. TECHNICAL ARCHITECTURE

### 3.1 Technology Stack

**Backend:**
- PHP 8.x with strict typing
- MySQL/MariaDB database
- PDO for database connectivity
- RESTful API architecture

**Frontend:**
- HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript (ES6+)
- Lucide Icons for UI elements
- Chart.js for data visualization
- Responsive design with mobile support

**Security:**
- CSRF protection
- Session hardening
- Input sanitization
- SQL injection prevention
- XSS protection

### 3.2 System Architecture Pattern
The system follows a Model-View-Controller (MVC) inspired architecture with:
- Modular page-based routing
- Centralized configuration management
- Component-based UI structure
- API-first design principles

### 3.3 Database Design
- Relational database with proper normalization
- Foreign key constraints for data integrity
- Comprehensive audit logging
- Optimized indexing for performance

